Task 3: Write Scripts to Automate Policy Enforcement
Subtask 3.1: Creating a User Management Script
Create a script to automate user creation with proper RBAC assignment:

nano ~/defense-lab/create-security-user.sh
Add the following script content:

#!/bin/bash

# Security User Creation Script
# Usage: ./create-security-user.sh <username> <role>

if [ $# -ne 2 ]; then
    echo "Usage: $0 <username> <role>"
    echo "Roles: admin, analyst, user"
    exit 1
fi

USERNAME=$1
ROLE=$2

case $ROLE in
    "admin")
        GROUP="security-admins"
        ;;
    "analyst")
        GROUP="security-analysts"
        ;;
    "user")
        GROUP="security-users"
        ;;
    *)
        echo "Invalid role. Use: admin, analyst, or user"
        exit 1
        ;;
esac

# Check if user already exists
if id "$USERNAME" &>/dev/null; then
    echo "User $USERNAME already exists"
    exit 1
fi

# Create user
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash -G $GROUP $USERNAME

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "User $USERNAME created successfully with role $ROLE"
    echo "Please set password for $USERNAME:"
    sudo passwd $USERNAME
    
    # Log the creation
    echo "$(date): User $USERNAME created with role $ROLE" | sudo tee -a /opt/security/logs/user-creation.log
else
    echo "Failed to create user $USERNAME"
    exit 1
fi
Make the script executable:

chmod +x ~/defense-lab/create-security-user.sh
Subtask 3.2: Creating a Security Audit Script
Create a script to audit system security settings:

nano ~/defense-lab/security-audit.sh
Add the following script content:

#!/bin/bash

# Security Audit Script
# Performs basic security checks on the system

AUDIT_LOG="/opt/security/logs/security-audit-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S).log"

echo "=== SECURITY AUDIT REPORT ===" | sudo tee $AUDIT_LOG
echo "Date: $(date)" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "System: $(hostname)" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

# Check user accounts
echo "=== USER ACCOUNTS ===" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "Security Admin Users:" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
getent group security-admins | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

echo "Security Analyst Users:" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
getent group security-analysts | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

echo "Security Regular Users:" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
getent group security-users | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

# Check file permissions on critical files
echo "=== CRITICAL FILE PERMISSIONS ===" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
ls -la /etc/passwd /etc/shadow /etc/sudoers | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

# Check security directory permissions
echo "=== SECURITY DIRECTORY PERMISSIONS ===" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
ls -la /opt/security/ | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

# Check firewall status
echo "=== FIREWALL STATUS ===" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
sudo ufw status | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

# Check for failed login attempts
echo "=== RECENT FAILED LOGIN ATTEMPTS ===" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
sudo grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log | tail -5 | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG
echo "" | sudo tee -a $AUDIT_LOG

echo "Audit completed. Report saved to: $AUDIT_LOG"
