Troubleshooting Tips
Common Issues and Solutions
Issue: Permission denied when running scripts Solution: Ensure scripts have execute permissions using chmod +x script-name.sh

Issue: Cannot access security directories Solution: Verify you are in the correct group using groups command and check directory permissions with ls -la

Issue: User creation fails Solution: Check if the user already exists with id username and ensure you have sudo privileges

Issue: Firewall commands fail Solution: Ensure UFW is installed with sudo apt update && sudo apt install ufw

Conclusion
In this lab, you have successfully implemented a comprehensive defense-in-depth security strategy on a single Linux system. You accomplished the following key objectives:

Defense-in-Depth Understanding: You learned that security is not a single barrier but multiple layers working together, from physical security to procedural controls.

RBAC Implementation: You created a functional Role-Based Access Control system with three distinct security roles (admin, analyst, user), each with appropriate permissions and access levels.

Automation and Policy Enforcement: You developed scripts that automate user management, security auditing, and policy enforcement, demonstrating how automation strengthens security posture.

Practical Security Skills: You gained hands-on experience with Linux security features, user management, file permissions, and system monitoring.

This defense-in-depth approach is crucial in real-world cybersecurity because attackers rarely succeed through a single point of failure. By implementing multiple security layers, you create a robust security posture where if one layer is compromised, others continue to protect the system.

The skills you developed in this lab form the foundation for more advanced cybersecurity practices and are directly applicable to enterprise security environments. The automation scripts you created demonstrate the importance of consistent policy enforcement and regular security auditing in maintaining a secure system.

Remember that defense-in-depth is an ongoing process, not a one-time implementation. Regular audits, policy updates, and continuous monitoring are essential components of an effective cybersecurity strategy.

